00:04:10.396 --> 00:04:12.176 A:middle
to the device, but we still get

00:04:12.176 --> 00:04:13.616 A:middle
that increased contrast and

00:04:13.616 --> 00:04:15.306 A:middle
legibility of having a solid

00:04:15.306 --> 00:04:15.756 A:middle
background.

00:04:17.146 --> 00:04:18.776 A:middle
As a developer, you can cater

00:04:18.776 --> 00:04:20.065 A:middle
your own use of blurring and

00:04:20.065 --> 00:04:21.846 A:middle
transparency by checking whether

00:04:21.846 --> 00:04:23.106 A:middle
or not the reduced transparency

00:04:23.106 --> 00:04:24.676 A:middle
setting is enabled and adapting

00:04:24.676 --> 00:04:25.596 A:middle
your UI accordingly.

00:04:26.316 --> 00:04:28.136 A:middle
On iOS, you would use is reduce

00:04:28.136 --> 00:04:29.866 A:middle
transparency enabled on UI

00:04:29.866 --> 00:04:32.576 A:middle
accessibility, and on macOS,

00:04:32.826 --> 00:04:34.326 A:middle
accessibility display should

00:04:34.326 --> 00:04:36.116 A:middle
reduce transparency on NS

00:04:36.116 --> 00:04:36.706 A:middle
Workspace.

00:04:38.116 --> 00:04:39.656 A:middle
Next, I'd like to talk about

00:04:39.656 --> 00:04:40.436 A:middle
contrast.

00:04:42.086 --> 00:04:43.756 A:middle
Contrast between content and

00:04:43.756 --> 00:04:45.486 A:middle
it's background is hugely

00:04:45.486 --> 00:04:46.506 A:middle
important when it comes to

00:04:46.506 --> 00:04:47.456 A:middle
perceivability.

00:04:47.976 --> 00:04:49.546 A:middle
As colors get closer to one

00:04:49.546 --> 00:04:51.106 A:middle
another, they become more

00:04:51.106 --> 00:04:52.406 A:middle
difficult to distinguish.

00:04:53.456 --> 00:04:54.886 A:middle
As well, certain colors that are

00:04:54.886 --> 00:04:56.756 A:middle
legible at bigger sizes don't

00:04:56.756 --> 00:04:58.056 A:middle
work when content is scaled

00:04:58.056 --> 00:04:58.436 A:middle
down.

00:04:58.676 --> 00:05:00.296 A:middle
For example, with text, the


00:04:58.676 --> 00:05:00.296 A:middle
For example, with text, the

00:05:00.296 --> 00:05:01.586 A:middle
letters bleed together more

00:05:01.586 --> 00:05:03.106 A:middle
easily at smaller sizes.

00:05:04.166 --> 00:05:06.026 A:middle
Now you can compute the contrast

00:05:06.026 --> 00:05:07.816 A:middle
ratio between a particular color

00:05:07.816 --> 00:05:09.436 A:middle
combination to see whether or

00:05:09.436 --> 00:05:10.886 A:middle
not it's going to be legible,

00:05:11.016 --> 00:05:12.046 A:middle
and we followed the

00:05:12.046 --> 00:05:13.406 A:middle
recommendations laid out in the

00:05:13.406 --> 00:05:14.796 A:middle
web content accessibility

00:05:14.796 --> 00:05:16.506 A:middle
guidelines that states that the

00:05:16.506 --> 00:05:18.296 A:middle
minimum contrast ratio you

00:05:18.296 --> 00:05:20.756 A:middle
should aim for is 4.5 to 1.

00:05:21.096 --> 00:05:23.836 A:middle
Obviously, the highest contrast

00:05:23.836 --> 00:05:24.766 A:middle
that you're going to be able to

00:05:24.766 --> 00:05:26.206 A:middle
get is between black and white,

00:05:26.676 --> 00:05:28.876 A:middle
which comes out to be 21 to 1

00:05:28.936 --> 00:05:30.566 A:middle
and obviously works great at all

00:05:30.566 --> 00:05:31.356 A:middle
text sizes.

00:05:32.186 --> 00:05:33.176 A:middle
Now let's take a look at a shade

00:05:33.176 --> 00:05:33.606 A:middle
of gray.

00:05:35.066 --> 00:05:36.386 A:middle
This particular gray will work

00:05:36.386 --> 00:05:38.506 A:middle
great for larger text, but it

00:05:38.506 --> 00:05:39.966 A:middle
isn't so great for smaller text

00:05:40.226 --> 00:05:40.996 A:middle
because your eyes can't

00:05:40.996 --> 00:05:41.966 A:middle
distinguish the shapes of the

00:05:41.966 --> 00:05:42.676 A:middle
letter forms.

00:05:43.066 --> 00:05:45.566 A:middle
It's contrast ratio 4.5 to 1 is

00:05:45.756 --> 00:05:47.246 A:middle
right on the line of passable.

00:05:48.186 --> 00:05:49.346 A:middle
Let's like take a look at one

00:05:49.346 --> 00:05:49.906 A:middle
last gray.

00:05:51.076 --> 00:05:52.686 A:middle
It may not be apparent on this

00:05:52.686 --> 00:05:55.926 A:middle
really large display, but this

00:05:55.926 --> 00:05:57.926 A:middle
text is really hard to see on a

00:05:57.926 --> 00:05:59.806 A:middle
small device, even at a large

00:05:59.806 --> 00:06:00.576 A:middle
font size.


00:05:59.806 --> 00:06:00.576 A:middle
font size.

00:06:01.126 --> 00:06:03.216 A:middle
It's contrast ratio of 2.9 to 1

00:06:03.216 --> 00:06:04.676 A:middle
is just too low.

00:06:04.676 --> 00:06:09.486 A:middle
And you can use the built-in

00:06:09.486 --> 00:06:11.106 A:middle
tool in our accessibility

00:06:11.106 --> 00:06:13.926 A:middle
inspector in Xcode to show you

00:06:13.926 --> 00:06:15.916 A:middle
what the contrast ratio between

00:06:16.286 --> 00:06:17.896 A:middle
a particular color combination

00:06:17.896 --> 00:06:19.856 A:middle
is and what text sizes that

00:06:19.856 --> 00:06:21.276 A:middle
color combo passes for.

00:06:21.276 --> 00:06:22.386 A:middle
And we follow the same

00:06:22.386 --> 00:06:23.456 A:middle
guidelines that I mentioned

00:06:23.456 --> 00:06:24.386 A:middle
before in this tool.

00:06:25.496 --> 00:06:27.016 A:middle
However, even with a ratio that

00:06:27.016 --> 00:06:29.736 A:middle
exceeds the recommended contrast

00:06:29.736 --> 00:06:32.766 A:middle
ratio of 4.5 to 1, for people

00:06:32.766 --> 00:06:34.186 A:middle
with low vision conditions,

00:06:34.676 --> 00:06:35.906 A:middle
colors that meet the bar can

00:06:35.906 --> 00:06:37.216 A:middle
still be problematic when it

00:06:37.216 --> 00:06:38.196 A:middle
comes to legibility.

00:06:39.316 --> 00:06:40.626 A:middle
So we provide a setting for

00:06:40.626 --> 00:06:42.266 A:middle
increasing the contrast across

00:06:42.266 --> 00:06:42.826 A:middle
the system.

00:06:43.536 --> 00:06:45.016 A:middle
In previous versions of iOS,

