text is on, then you can check

00:08:43.826 --> 00:08:44.646 A:middle
whether or not the setting is

00:08:44.646 --> 00:08:46.336 A:middle
enabled and adapt as necessary.

00:08:46.806 --> 00:08:50.096 A:middle
Next, we have motion.

00:08:51.106 --> 00:08:53.606 A:middle
Animation is fun, and it often

00:08:53.606 --> 00:08:55.096 A:middle
makes content feel more alive.

00:08:55.096 --> 00:08:57.006 A:middle
It can provide a direct

00:08:57.006 --> 00:08:58.976 A:middle
correlation between user

00:08:58.976 --> 00:09:00.876 A:middle
interaction and what effects


00:08:58.976 --> 00:09:00.876 A:middle
interaction and what effects

00:09:00.876 --> 00:09:02.076 A:middle
their actions are having.

00:09:02.966 --> 00:09:04.316 A:middle
However, certain conditions,

00:09:04.316 --> 00:09:05.516 A:middle
particularly inner ear

00:09:05.516 --> 00:09:07.236 A:middle
conditions that affect the

00:09:07.236 --> 00:09:09.116 A:middle
balance center of the brain can

00:09:09.116 --> 00:09:10.426 A:middle
make motion and animation

00:09:10.426 --> 00:09:12.786 A:middle
problematic, which often results

00:09:12.786 --> 00:09:14.416 A:middle
in things like dizziness or

00:09:14.416 --> 00:09:15.916 A:middle
imbalance or even nausea.

00:09:17.546 --> 00:09:18.876 A:middle
Now I'm going to go through some

00:09:18.876 --> 00:09:20.396 A:middle
examples of animation types that

00:09:20.396 --> 00:09:22.636 A:middle
can be problematic, so if any of

00:09:22.636 --> 00:09:23.556 A:middle
you in the audience have a

00:09:23.556 --> 00:09:25.316 A:middle
problem with motion, then you

00:09:25.316 --> 00:09:26.266 A:middle
may want to look away

00:09:26.266 --> 00:09:27.256 A:middle
momentarily as I play the

00:09:27.256 --> 00:09:28.836 A:middle
default animations, which I am

00:09:28.836 --> 00:09:29.806 A:middle
going to preface.

00:09:30.946 --> 00:09:32.876 A:middle
The first is scaling and

00:09:32.876 --> 00:09:33.466 A:middle
zooming.

00:09:34.026 --> 00:09:35.656 A:middle
On the left, we have the default

00:09:35.656 --> 00:09:36.936 A:middle
animation for opening an app,

00:09:37.476 --> 00:09:38.736 A:middle
specifically the clock app,

00:09:39.166 --> 00:09:40.106 A:middle
which I'm going to show now.

00:09:41.816 --> 00:09:43.156 A:middle
We zoom into the location of the

00:09:43.156 --> 00:09:45.176 A:middle
app's icon while it's UI scales

00:09:45.176 --> 00:09:45.756 A:middle
into view.

00:09:46.206 --> 00:09:47.286 A:middle
And on the right, we have the

00:09:47.286 --> 00:09:48.856 A:middle
same interaction but with reduce

00:09:48.856 --> 00:09:50.556 A:middle
motion enabled, which will

00:09:50.556 --> 00:09:52.186 A:middle
replace that with a simple cross

00:09:52.866 --> 00:09:52.966 A:middle
fade.

00:09:54.236 --> 00:09:56.306 A:middle
Next, spinning and vortex

00:09:56.306 --> 00:09:56.776 A:middle
effects.

00:09:57.316 --> 00:09:58.826 A:middle
If we take a look at the full

00:09:58.826 --> 00:10:00.726 A:middle
screen echo effect in messages,


00:09:58.826 --> 00:10:00.726 A:middle
screen echo effect in messages,

00:10:00.726 --> 00:10:02.756 A:middle
which I'm going to show now, we

00:10:02.756 --> 00:10:04.336 A:middle
can see that content is spinning

00:10:04.336 --> 00:10:06.006 A:middle
along the Z axis while also

00:10:06.006 --> 00:10:07.816 A:middle
changing in scale, and these

00:10:07.816 --> 00:10:09.096 A:middle
types of motions paired together

00:10:09.096 --> 00:10:10.116 A:middle
can cause issues.

00:10:10.966 --> 00:10:12.556 A:middle
In the case of message effects,

00:10:12.616 --> 00:10:14.006 A:middle
if reduced motion is enabled,

00:10:14.006 --> 00:10:15.476 A:middle
then we provide the user with a

00:10:15.476 --> 00:10:18.086 A:middle
specific prompt to play the

00:10:18.086 --> 00:10:19.786 A:middle
message effect instead of having

00:10:19.786 --> 00:10:20.506 A:middle
it autoplay.

00:10:20.576 --> 00:10:21.426 A:middle
So they can choose whether or

00:10:21.426 --> 00:10:23.076 A:middle
not they want to see it.

00:10:24.396 --> 00:10:25.556 A:middle
Next, we have plane-shifting

00:10:25.556 --> 00:10:26.316 A:middle
animations.

00:10:26.986 --> 00:10:28.116 A:middle
What I want to show here is the

00:10:28.116 --> 00:10:29.616 A:middle
Safari tabs animation.

00:10:29.896 --> 00:10:31.336 A:middle
So I'm going to tap on the show

00:10:31.336 --> 00:10:33.346 A:middle
tabs button, and you see that

00:10:33.346 --> 00:10:34.786 A:middle
the plane of the web cards is

00:10:34.786 --> 00:10:36.726 A:middle
shifted to simulate a 3D space.

00:10:37.496 --> 00:10:38.696 A:middle
And on the right, we have the

00:10:38.696 --> 00:10:40.486 A:middle
reduced animation, which again

00:10:40.486 --> 00:10:42.536 A:middle
is a simple cross fade, but we

00:10:42.536 --> 00:10:44.996 A:middle
also blink the card so that you

00:10:44.996 --> 00:10:46.666 A:middle
have the context of which one

00:10:46.666 --> 00:10:49.536 A:middle
you're coming from that you got

00:10:50.226 --> 00:10:53.000 A:middle
in the original animation.

00:10:54.286 --> 00:10:56.186 A:middle
Multidirectional or multispeed

00:10:56.246 --> 00:10:57.636 A:middle
motion is another trigger.

00:10:58.366 --> 00:10:59.496 A:middle
I'm going to show the movement

00:10:59.496 --> 00:11:00.646 A:middle
of the messages bubbles in a


00:10:59.496 --> 00:11:00.646 A:middle
of the messages bubbles in a

00:11:00.646 --> 00:11:01.466 A:middle
conversation.

00:11:01.996 --> 00:11:03.286 A:middle
It's a little hard to see in

00:11:03.286 --> 00:11:04.416 A:middle
this video, but it's a lot more

00:11:04.416 --> 00:11:05.516 A:middle
obvious on device.

00:11:06.196 --> 00:11:08.306 A:middle
As I scroll the messages, they

00:11:08.306 --> 00:11:09.916 A:middle
have a springiness to them where

00:11:09.916 --> 00:11:12.196 A:middle
they contract and expand away

00:11:12.196 --> 00:11:14.576 A:middle
from one another.

00:11:14.626 --> 00:11:15.866 A:middle
If we have reduce motion

00:11:15.866 --> 00:11:17.706 A:middle
enabled, then we disable this

00:11:17.706 --> 00:11:19.236 A:middle
effect and have them just scroll

00:11:19.236 --> 00:11:19.636 A:middle
normally.

00:11:22.476 --> 00:11:24.486 A:middle
Finally, we have peripheral

00:11:24.486 --> 00:11:25.006 A:middle
movement.

00:11:26.016 --> 00:11:27.536 A:middle
The weather app on iOS has

00:11:27.536 --> 00:11:29.106 A:middle
subtle animations that play in

00:11:29.106 --> 00:11:30.756 A:middle
the background to indicate the

00:11:30.756 --> 00:11:32.166 A:middle
current weather condition.

00:11:32.616 --> 00:11:33.596 A:middle
You cans see on the left that

00:11:33.596 --> 00:11:35.146 A:middle
the clouds are sort of drifting

00:11:35.146 --> 00:11:36.296 A:middle
through the air and the sun is

00:11:36.296 --> 00:11:38.416 A:middle
sort of shimmering and shining.

00:11:38.626 --> 00:11:39.816 A:middle
But if you're scanning the

00:11:39.816 --> 00:11:41.086 A:middle
forecast below, then this

00:11:41.086 --> 00:11:43.026 A:middle
animation is in your peripheral

00:11:43.026 --> 00:11:44.526 A:middle
view, and this can be

00:11:44.526 --> 00:11:46.226 A:middle
problematic in the same way that

00:11:46.226 --> 00:11:48.176 A:middle
reading while riding in a car

00:11:48.366 --> 00:11:49.406 A:middle
can make you feel sick.

00:11:50.056 --> 00:11:51.656 A:middle
The horizontal motion above your

00:11:51.656 --> 00:11:53.036 A:middle
area of focus triggers a

00:11:53.036 --> 00:11:54.386 A:middle
reaction in your brain.

00:11:55.016 --> 00:11:56.806 A:middle
With reduced motion on, we

00:11:56.806 --> 00:11:57.686 A:middle
disable the background

00:11:57.686 --> 00:11:58.276 A:middle
animation.

00:11:58.826 --> 00:12:01.326 A:middle
Now typically we don't want to


00:11:58.826 --> 00:12:01.326 A:middle
Now typically we don't want to

00:12:01.326 --> 00:12:03.766 A:middle
just remove all animation, so of

00:12:03.766 --> 00:12:04.576 A:middle
course we have a setting that

00:12:04.576 --> 00:12:05.816 A:middle
you can check to see if motion

00:12:05.816 --> 00:12:07.566 A:middle
should be reduced and adapt

00:12:07.566 --> 00:12:08.186 A:middle
accordingly.

00:12:09.116 --> 00:12:10.596 A:middle
On iOS, you check is reduced

00:12:10.596 --> 00:12:12.926 A:middle
motion enabled, and on macOS,

00:12:13.136 --> 00:12:14.606 A:middle
check accessibility display

00:12:14.606 --> 00:12:15.606 A:middle
should reduce motion.

00:12:16.516 --> 00:12:18.046 A:middle
It's important to note that

00:12:18.046 --> 00:12:19.936 A:middle
simply removing an animation is

00:12:19.936 --> 00:12:21.216 A:middle
often not an adequate

00:12:21.266 --> 00:12:22.076 A:middle
experience.

00:12:22.666 --> 00:12:23.966 A:middle
You don't want to lessen the

00:12:23.966 --> 00:12:24.686 A:middle
experience.

00:12:24.686 --> 00:12:27.156 A:middle
You just want to add something

00:12:27.156 --> 00:12:28.806 A:middle
else equally fun or engaging but

00:12:28.806 --> 00:12:29.876 A:middle
different that works for the

00:12:29.876 --> 00:12:30.266 A:middle
user.

00:12:31.736 --> 00:12:33.416 A:middle
Finally, I'd like to finish

00:12:33.416 --> 00:12:34.586 A:middle
talking about design by

00:12:34.586 --> 00:12:36.306 A:middle
addressing UI complexity.

00:12:36.866 --> 00:12:39.236 A:middle
Apps play key roles in our lives

00:12:39.236 --> 00:12:40.696 A:middle
now, and it's critically

00:12:40.696 --> 00:12:42.366 A:middle
important for all of us that our

00:12:42.366 --> 00:12:44.246 A:middle
technology is simple and easy to

00:12:44.246 --> 00:12:46.646 A:middle
use, that it enhances our lives

00:12:46.646 --> 00:12:47.856 A:middle
instead of adding extra

00:12:47.856 --> 00:12:48.836 A:middle
unnecessary burden.

00:12:48.836 --> 00:12:52.336 A:middle
In the United States alone, one

00:12:52.336 --> 00:12:53.336 A:middle
in six children have a

00:12:53.336 --> 00:12:55.276 A:middle
developmental disability ranging

00:12:55.276 --> 00:12:56.306 A:middle
from speech and language

00:12:56.306 --> 00:12:58.016 A:middle
impairments to more serious

00:12:58.016 --> 00:12:59.306 A:middle
developmental disabilities like

00:12:59.306 --> 00:12:59.896 A:middle
autism.


00:13:00.576 --> 00:13:01.696 A:middle
For people with cognitive

00:13:01.696 --> 00:13:03.446 A:middle
disabilities or even a chronic

00:13:03.446 --> 00:13:06.156 A:middle
illness, using an app can expend

00:13:06.156 --> 00:13:07.716 A:middle
more energy than for someone who

00:13:07.716 --> 00:13:08.526 A:middle
is neurotypical.

00:13:09.356 --> 00:13:11.116 A:middle
So how do we make sure that our

00:13:11.116 --> 00:13:12.686 A:middle
apps are simple and the least

00:13:12.686 --> 00:13:13.826 A:middle
burdensome that they can be?

00:13:15.346 --> 00:13:16.596 A:middle
Well they should be easy to

00:13:16.596 --> 00:13:17.936 A:middle
navigate by having them

00:13:17.936 --> 00:13:19.696 A:middle
similarly structured and through

00:13:19.696 --> 00:13:21.676 A:middle
clear, logical cause and effect.

00:13:23.216 --> 00:13:24.496 A:middle
We should be able to start using

00:13:24.496 --> 00:13:26.136 A:middle
our apps and complete the most

00:13:26.136 --> 00:13:27.496 A:middle
common tasks without

00:13:27.496 --> 00:13:28.946 A:middle
encountering any barriers.

00:13:30.156 --> 00:13:31.506 A:middle
And finally, our apps should

00:13:31.506 --> 00:13:33.756 A:middle
behave in a consistent manner so

00:13:33.756 --> 00:13:35.076 A:middle
that when I learn something one

00:13:35.076 --> 00:13:36.976 A:middle
place, it applies to another.

00:13:37.666 --> 00:13:39.366 A:middle
Using this standard UIKit views

00:13:39.366 --> 00:13:40.906 A:middle
is great because people get

00:13:40.906 --> 00:13:43.416 A:middle
familiar with way they work, but

00:13:43.416 --> 00:13:45.166 A:middle
UIKit also functions as a design

00:13:45.166 --> 00:13:46.256 A:middle
language for iOS.

00:13:46.746 --> 00:13:47.666 A:middle
So if you're doing something

00:13:47.666 --> 00:13:49.566 A:middle
custom, consistency with a

00:13:49.566 --> 00:13:51.966 A:middle
parallel control in UIKit will

00:13:51.966 --> 00:13:53.336 A:middle
help people intuit how to use

00:13:53.336 --> 00:13:55.186 A:middle
your app.

00:13:55.336 --> 00:13:56.496 A:middle
This really all boils down to

00:13:56.496 --> 00:13:57.486 A:middle
the way in which people

00:13:57.486 --> 00:13:59.326 A:middle
experience your apps, which is

00:13:59.326 --> 00:14:00.506 A:middle
just as important for people who


00:13:59.326 --> 00:14:00.506 A:middle
just as important for people who

00:14:00.506 --> 00:14:01.966 A:middle
use assistive technologies like

00:14:01.966 --> 00:14:03.236 A:middle
VoiceOver or Switch Control.

00:14:04.206 --> 00:14:05.486 A:middle
So I'd like now to spend some

00:14:05.486 --> 00:14:06.616 A:middle
time speaking to how you can

00:14:06.616 --> 00:14:08.216 A:middle
improve the experience for those

00:14:08.216 --> 00:14:09.426 A:middle
accessibility users.

00:14:10.626 --> 00:14:12.306 A:middle
The experience for assistive

00:14:12.306 --> 00:14:13.796 A:middle
tech like VoiceOver and Switch

00:14:13.796 --> 00:14:15.346 A:middle
Control can be quite different

00:14:15.346 --> 00:14:16.476 A:middle
from your typical user

00:14:16.476 --> 00:14:17.256 A:middle
experience.

00:14:17.836 --> 00:14:19.326 A:middle
VoiceOver uses many gestures

00:14:19.326 --> 00:14:21.256 A:middle
like swipes and multifinger

00:14:22.426 --> 00:14:22.556 A:middle
taps,

00:14:25.076 --> 00:14:26.806 A:middle
while Switch Control scans

00:14:26.806 --> 00:14:28.516 A:middle
groups and offers logical quick

00:14:28.516 --> 00:14:29.256 A:middle
actions.

00:14:29.726 --> 00:14:31.386 A:middle
For both, there are built-in

00:14:31.386 --> 00:14:32.756 A:middle
equivalents for any standard

00:14:32.756 --> 00:14:35.626 A:middle
gesture or interaction, but what

00:14:35.626 --> 00:14:37.086 A:middle
makes experiencing an app with

00:14:37.086 --> 00:14:38.446 A:middle
these technologies exceptional?

00:14:39.536 --> 00:14:40.486 A:middle
We want to go from the bare

00:14:40.486 --> 00:14:43.576 A:middle
minimum of it works to it works

00:14:43.576 --> 00:14:43.896 A:middle
well.

00:14:45.766 --> 00:14:46.736 A:middle
While despite the fact that

00:14:46.736 --> 00:14:48.486 A:middle
assistive tech users experience

00:14:48.486 --> 00:14:49.996 A:middle
your app in ways that are

00:14:49.996 --> 00:14:51.756 A:middle
different, the same design

00:14:51.756 --> 00:14:53.256 A:middle
principles that drive a good

00:14:53.256 --> 00:14:53.976 A:middle
experience for a

00:14:53.976 --> 00:14:55.646 A:middle
nonaccessibility user applies

00:14:55.646 --> 00:14:55.906 A:middle
here.

00:14:56.646 --> 00:14:58.146 A:middle
You want easy navigation,

00:14:58.526 --> 00:14:59.726 A:middle
predictable behavior,

00:14:59.926 --> 00:15:02.386 A:middle
prioritizing our action, and


00:14:59.926 --> 00:15:02.386 A:middle
prioritizing our action, and

00:15:02.386 --> 00:15:02.996 A:middle
consistency.

00:15:04.086 --> 00:15:05.606 A:middle
It's also important to note that

00:15:05.606 --> 00:15:06.966 A:middle
if something is communicated

00:15:06.966 --> 00:15:08.416 A:middle
contextually by separate

00:15:08.416 --> 00:15:10.496 A:middle
elements, that same context is

00:15:10.496 --> 00:15:11.636 A:middle
conveyed to our accessibility

00:15:11.636 --> 00:15:12.166 A:middle
users.

00:15:13.136 --> 00:15:14.726 A:middle
I'd like now to bring Bhavya up

